{
  "title": "ISic001314. Funerary inscription for Myrtale",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Θ</span>(εοῖς) <span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Κ</span>(αταχθονίοις) <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μυρτάλη\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μυρτάλη\">Μυρτάλη</span></span> χρηστο-<br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>τάτη ἔζησεν ἔτη <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">λ</span>´ μῆν(ας) <span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">γ</span>´ <span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Κορνήλι\n                    ος Ἀγαθήμερος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κορνήλι\n                    ος\">Κορνήλι-<br id=\"al5-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span>ος</span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀγαθήμερος\">Ἀγαθήμερος</span></span> συν-<br id=\"al6-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span>βίῳ εὐσεβεστάτῃ ❦ <br id=\"al7-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">7</span>❦ ἐποίησε ❦ </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: #JP</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Θ</span><span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Κ</span>  <br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μυρτάλη\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μυρτάλη\">ΜΥΡΤΑΛΗ</span></span>ΧΡΗΣΤΟ<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span>ΤΑΤΗΕΖΗΣΕΝΕΤΗ<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Λ</span>ΜΗΝ<span class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">Γ</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Κορνήλι\n                    ος Ἀγαθήμερος\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κορνήλι\n                    ος\">ΚΟΡΝΗΛΙ<br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span>ΟΣ</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ἀγαθήμερος\">ΑΓΑΘΗΜΕΡΟΣ</span></span>ΣΥΝ<br id=\"al6-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">6</span>ΒΙΩΕΥΣΕΒΕΣΤΑΤΗ❦<br id=\"al7-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">7</span>❦ΕΠΟΙΗΣΕ❦</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic001314_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001314_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic001314.jpg\"><img title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001314-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text from photograph</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>To the gods of the underworld. Myrtale, most worthy, lived for 30 years, 3 months. Kornelios Agathemeros made this for his most devoted partner in life.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>Italian translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">Serena Agodi</p>  <p>Agli dèi del mondo sotterraneo. Myrtale, degnissima, visse 30 anni e 3 mesi. Kornelios Agathemeros lo ha fatto per la sua devotissima compagna di vita.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p> This epitaph was found together with IG 14.485 (exhibition no.26), which was apparently erected in memory of the same man as set up this text (although it is also possible that they are father and son). The implication is that Myrtale was his first wife and that he remarried (to Euphrosyne) after her death. The differing letter forms and use of Greek numerals indicate that this was engraved by a different stonemason.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Franz 1853 5717 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250</a></li><li> Kaibel 1890 <a href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">492</a>  <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072</a></li><li> Korhonen 2004 111 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p> Line 1  16-22  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not measured  </p></div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
